  "prompt": "How do I write answer in engineering exams in English being gujrati medium student?",
  "response": "Writing answers in English during engineering exams as a Gujarati medium student can be challenging, but with practice and effective strategies, you can improve your skills. Here are some tips to help you:\n\n1. **Understand the Question**:\n   - Read the question carefully to grasp what is being asked before you start writing your answer.\n\n2. **Plan Your Answer**:\n   - Outline your answer briefly. Identify the main points you want to cover and organize them logically. This will help you stay focused while writing.\n\n3. **Use Simple Language**:\n   - Since your primary language is Gujarati, it's okay to use simple English. Focus on conveying your ideas clearly rather than trying to use complex vocabulary.\n\n4. **Practice Technical Vocabulary**:\n   - Familiarize yourself with key engineering terms and phrases in English. Make a list of commonly used terms and try to use them in your answers. \n\n5. **Write Clear Sentences**:\n   - Start your sentences with a subject and a verb. Keep them short and to the point. This will help reduce grammatical errors and improve readability.\n\n6. **Use Diagrams and Equations**:\n   - Engineering often involves diagrams and equations. Use these to support your answers when applicable, as they can convey information effectively and can sometimes compensate for language limitations.\n\n7. **Practice Writing**:\n   - Regularly practice writing answers in English. You can start with simpler topics and gradually move to more complex ones. \n\n8. **Review Previous Exam Papers**:\n   - Look at past exam questions and answers. This will give you an idea of how to structure your responses and the kind of vocabulary typically used.\n\n9. **Get Feedback**:\n   - If possible, ask your teachers or peers to review your answers and provide feedback. They can help you identify areas for improvement.\n\n10. **Use Study Groups**:\n    - Join study groups with classmates who are proficient in English. Discussing concepts and answering questions together can improve your understanding and language skills.\n\n11. **Stay Calm and Confident**:\n    - During the exam, stay calm and trust in your preparation. If you have practiced writing in English, you will be more confident in expressing your knowledge.\n\n12. **Proofread Your Answers**:\n    - If time permits, quickly review your answers. Look for spelling mistakes and unclear sentences, and make necessary corrections.\n\nBy implementing these strategies and providing consistent effort, you'll become more comfortable writing your engineering exam answers in English. Good luck!",
